  "prompt": "Do US presidents get bodyguard protection after they have left the office?",
  "response": "Yes, former U.S. presidents are entitled to receive bodyguard protection after leaving office, but the extent and duration of that protection have varied over time. The Former Presidents Act of 1958 provides for lifetime protection for former presidents, although this was changed in 1994 when Congress limited protection for presidents who leave office after January 1, 1997, to a period of 10 years. However, former presidents may still receive lifetime protection under certain circumstances, particularly if there are specific threats to their safety. \n\nAdditionally, former vice presidents also receive some level of protection, though it is not as extensive or long-lasting as that provided to former presidents.",
